post_text:
We are ready for the 2020 Graduation tomorrow. Just a few reminders:
1. Graduates and their guests should arrive no earlier than 10:15 AM and should park in their assigned lot.
2. Graduates should wait until all of their guests have arrived and should enter the field together.
3. The seating has been arranged in groups of 5 so graduates will sit with their guests.
4. Graduates and their guests are required to wear masks and maintain social distancing between groups.
5. A live link for viewing the ceremony is available (see a previous post on this page).
6. Please forward any questions to Ted Zawada: zawadat@lpsma.net

Here is a link to a Senior slide show:
https://drive.google.com/file/d/13Yyval0AqNZC8vDxf5bh5Z3FsrapYbjC/view?usp=sharing

We look forward to seeing you all on this long-awaited day.

We understand the restrictions that Covid-19 has brought to our graduation and we want to accommodate all individuals that would like to view the event at home. post_text: Every year during the 8th Grade graduation, Leicester Middle School recognizes a member of the community for the outstanding volunteer work they have done for the students of Leicester Middle School. This year's Linda Colby Volunteer award goes to Officer James Murphy for his dedication to help the students of LMS through the DARE program and other things he has done within the school. He is known throughout the school for his kindness and work that he does. Thank you, Officer Murphy!

post_text: Last night, Friends of Leicester Middle School hosted its first of two annual Dodgeball Fun Nights. It was a blast. Over 200 students and staff played and many more came out to watch. See you in the spring!

post_text: Earlier this year, Friends of Leicester Middle School applied for a grant from the Osterman Family Foundation and received $12,500. The money is being used to fund the LMS Innovation Hub, which consists of four after-school enrichment clubs and activities: the Movie Club, the AV Club, the MakerSpace, and the Robotics Club. So far, three of these clubs are up and running, and the fourth is scheduled to start up this fall. Recently, we had to provide the foundation with a progress report on how the money is being used. If you would like to find out about all the fantastic things that have happened because of this investment in LMS, just click on the following link.

post_text: For the third year in a row, the Greater Worcester Community Foundation through Leicester Savings Bank has funded LMS CommuniTeen. CommuniTeen's mission is to change the world by helping family, friends, and neighbors. The main goal of LMS CommuniTeen is to supplement academic learning by providing meaningful service learning activities, which encourage and enable students to positively impact their community and grow hearts for service. More importantly, the program teaches good citizenship and educates students to become the change agents of tomorrow. Thanks, again, Leicester Savings Bank!

post_text: The Middle School is doing something so fabulous it is hard to describe in words. They are creating and producing an original film based on the popular Harry Potter series. The teachers have been working on it for months, and today was a huge filming day at The Castle Restaurant. About 80 students and a group of teachers showed up to be in the film, and a couple of high school students did the filming. The costumes and the setting were magical. Many townspeople donated props, and the flags that hung from the rafters were designed by the students. Our hats are off to Jamie DePace, STEM teacher, and Christy Minton, library/media specialist, for conceiving of this plan and to all the teachers and staff who showed up to participate on their day off. We especially want to thank the Nicas family, James, Denise, and Evangeline, for hosting the Middle School today. We can't wait to see the final production. This is authentic learning at its best!

The School Committee will hold a Workshop at 5:00 pm on Monday, February 4, 2019 in the High School library. One of the topics to be discussed is the Memorial School and also on the agenda is the FY 2020 budget. You are welcome to attend. High school students will be on hand to provide babysitting services.

***********************************************

As a reminder, the next meeting of the Superintendent's Advisory Council will be held on Wednesday, February 6, 2019 at 3:30 pm in the library at the High School. All are welcome. I hope to see you there.

Marilyn Tencza
Superintendent
